<BaseLayout title="Shelf">
    <p>Various artistic works I'm fond of.</p>
    <p>
        This is not meant to be a complete list of favorites. It's closer to a
        shelf: stories, images, scenes, and other things I like enough to keep
        around. If you ever wanted to chat with me on a casual basis, chances
        are I would probably enjoy discussing something on this shelf.
    </p>
    <p>
        This page contains no major spoilers that aren't gated behind a spoiler
        warning, so there shouldn't be any risk in reading about any piece of
        media you haven't finished.
    </p>

    <h2>Steel Ball Run</h2>

    <p>
        Steel Ball Run is probably the closest thing I currently have to a
        "favorite piece of media." As the seventh installment of the JoJo's
        Bizarre Adventure franchise, I consider it the pinnacle of storytelling,
        art, and character progression of the series.
    </p>
    <p>
        While the art style of the JoJo's manga has evolved continuously over
        time, this part's style is definitely my favorite. The level of detail
        and polish on every page grew exponentially after the manga switched to
        a monthly magazine, a level that I believe is unmatched even by Part 8
        and Part 9.
    </p>
    <p>
        My specific favorite style is the style that was used near the middle of
        the manga, or around the Sugar Mountain arc. It's a great balance
        between linework, proportions, expressive faces, and facial
        distinguishability.
    </p>

