    <h2>Chainsaw Man</h2>

    <p>
        Chainsaw Man is a two-part manga series created by Tatsuki Fujimoto. I
        really enjoyed how it handled insatiable desire, the idea that with
        every granted wish, a person only becomes increasingly greedier, until
        they lose it all.
    </p>
    <p>
        My favorite segment of the manga has to be early Part 2. The possession
        of Asa Mitaka by Yoru keeps the tension at a constant high, contrasting
        beautifully with the low-stakes slow-burn high school environment.
    </p>
    <p>
        I'm also a big fan of Fujimoto's art style. Despite being highly
        stylized, it manages to portray its characters in a way that feels
        realistic and visceral. Elsewhere, the art style of Season 1 of the
        anime creates an atmosphere that I think is perfect for the story. I'm
        looking forward to seeing Fujimoto's future works, and the upcoming
        adaptation of the International Assassins arc by MAPPA.
    </p>
